MULLIGAN SOLAR, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Mulligan Solar, LLC ("Mulligan Solar") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Mulligan Solar generating facility ("Mulligan Solar Facility").
Mulligan Solar is a solar generating facility located in Logan County, Illinois. The Mulligan Solar Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Ameren Illinois Company and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Mulligan Solar's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Mulligan Solar Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Mulligan Solar's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Mulligan Solar shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $345,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $28,750.00.
